A constructor is defined within a class as follows:
class ClassName {
public:
  ClassName() {} // Default constructor
  ClassName(data_type param) {} // Parameterized constructor
};
- **ClassName()**: Default constructor, creates an object without parameters.
- **ClassName(data_type param)**: Parameterized constructor, initializes with specific values.
Constructors are called automatically when an object is created.

